            "text_xyE6Aw": {
              "type": "text",
              "name": "t:names.description",
              "settings": {
                "text": "<h2><strong>What goes in, and why</strong></h2><p>Biota<strong>derm</strong> rests on three things, and they form part of every formulation.</p><p><strong>Nature.</strong> Cold-pressed organic plant oils as the backbone, carefully blended with supporting natural and naturally derived ingredients.</p><p><strong>Science.</strong> Ingredients selected because the published evidence supports them, including prebiotics and postbiotics to help feed and steady the community of microbes living on your skin. The research on the skin microbiome is still being mapped, and we'd rather say that honestly than overstate it.</p><p><strong>Ethics.</strong> Vegan-friendly, never tested on animals (other than the willing humans in this house), packed by hand, and working towards B Corp certification the slow and effective way.</p><p>Bladderwrack runs through the range, the same Atlantic seaweed you've stepped over on every rocky beach in Devon. Ours is processed in France by specialist extractors who work with the same species we see at low tide. The research on it is genuinely exciting, which is the main reason it's in here.</p>",
                "width": "100%",
                "max_width": "normal",
                "alignment": "left",
                "type_preset": "rte",
                "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
