              "type": "text",
              "name": "t:names.description",
              "settings": {
                "text": "<h2><strong>A note from Richard: every sale, up to 15th July, gives half to Devon Air Ambulance</strong></h2><p>From launch up to and including the 15th of July, half of every sale goes to Devon Air Ambulance.</p><p>Here's the part I'm slightly nervous about though! The 4th of July is the day I take on the Devon Air Ambulance Heli Hike. Twenty-six miles along the South West Coast Path, with enough climbing in it to add up to Ben Nevis by the time I'm done. Devon Air Ambulance covers this stretch of coast, the home of Biota<strong>derm</strong>, and they do it without government funding. Backing them felt like the right way to begin.</p><p>So if you buy something in those first few weeks, you've quietly done two good things at once. Looked after your skin, and helped keep a helicopter in the air over Devon.</p>",
